<section class="container py-5">

    <!-- TOP NAV ACTIONS -->
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-end mb-3">
        <% if (isLoggedIn) { %>
            <a href="/" class="btn btn-dark me-3">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-house"></i> Home
            </a>
            <a href="/dashboard" class="btn btn-primary ">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-chart-line"></i> Dashboard
            </a>
        <% } else { %>
            <a href="/" class="btn btn-dark ">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-house"></i> Home
            </a>
        <% } %>
    </div>

    <!-- HEADER -->
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <h1 class="fw-bold">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved me-2"></i> Security Architecture
        </h1>
        <p class="text-muted">
            A detailed overview of how PassVault ensures confidentiality, integrity, and security of user data.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- ================= FLOW DIAGRAM ================= -->
    <div class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-diagram-project me-2 text-primary"></i> System Flow
        </h3>

        <div class="flow-box mt-4">

            <div class="flow-step">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-user-lock"></i>
                <p>User Login</p>
            </div>

            <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right flow-arrow"></i>

            <div class="flow-step">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-key"></i>
                <p>Key Derivation<br>(PBKDF2)</p>
            </div>

            <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right flow-arrow"></i>

            <div class="flow-step">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-lock"></i>
                <p>AES Encryption</p>
            </div>

            <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right flow-arrow"></i>

            <div class="flow-step">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-database"></i>
                <p>Secure Storage</p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ================= ENCRYPTION ================= -->
    <div class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-lock me-2 text-success"></i> Encryption Strategy
        </h3>
        <p>
            Sensitive user credentials are encrypted using AES-256 encryption before being stored.
            The encryption key is derived dynamically using PBKDF2 from the user's master password.
            This ensures that even the server cannot decrypt stored data without user input.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- ================= WHY AES + PBKDF2 ================= -->
    <div class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info me-2 text-warning"></i> Why AES + PBKDF2?
        </h3>

        <ul>
            <li><strong>AES-256:</strong> Industry-standard symmetric encryption, fast and secure.</li>
            <li><strong>PBKDF2:</strong> Protects against brute-force attacks using key stretching.</li>
            <li><strong>No Key Storage:</strong> Encryption key is never stored in database.</li>
            <li><strong>Defense in Depth:</strong> Combines hashing + encryption for maximum security.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- ================= THREAT MODEL ================= -->
    <div class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-triangle-exclamation me-2 text-danger"></i> Threat Model
        </h3>

        <div class="row">

            <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                <div class="threat-card">
                    <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-user-secret me-2"></i> Data Breach</h6>
                    <p>Encrypted data ensures attackers cannot read credentials.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                <div class="threat-card">
                    <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-bug me-2"></i> Brute Force</h6>
                    <p>Rate limiting and PBKDF2 reduce attack feasibility.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                <div class="threat-card">
                    <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-network-wired me-2"></i> Session Hijacking</h6>
                    <p>Secure cookies and session tracking mitigate risks.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                <div class="threat-card">
                    <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-location-dot me-2"></i> Suspicious Login</h6>
                    <p>OTP verification triggers on device/location changes.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ================= SESSION ================= -->
    <div class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-laptop me-2 text-info"></i> Session Security
        </h3>
        <p>
            Sessions are securely stored using MongoDB. Users can monitor and revoke sessions across devices.
            Sessions expire automatically and inactive sessions are cleaned periodically.
        </p>
    </div>

</section>